  "warnings": [
    "CRP is nonspecific and must be interpreted in clinical context.",
    "In neonates, a physiological increase in CRP can occur within the first 24-48 hours of life, but values persistently >10 mg/L or a rapidly rising trend should be evaluated for early-onset sepsis."
  ],
  "notes": [
    "Standard CRP reference limits are generally independent of age and sex after the immediate postnatal period.",
    "For cardiovascular risk assessment, High-Sensitivity CRP (hs-CRP) should be used, which has distinct lower-tier interpretive ranges."
